Output:

```
Raw URL parser results:
  Query: Some("")
  Fragment: Some("fragment=thing&q1=v1")
Iron URL parser results:
  Query: Some("")
  Fragment: Some("fragment=thing&q1=v1")
```

As you can see, all the data after the `#` gets dumped into the fragment field. This is part of the WHATWG URL spec: https://url.spec.whatwg.org/#query-state

Once the URL parsing state machine enters the fragment state it treats all subsequent characters as part of the the fragment, and there's no way to get back to the query state to parse the `&q1=v1` part.

